                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 5:14:57 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> About Katta<br /><br />Theres still work arounds now that they "fixed" fear pathing. For instance. Last nite at the bank. I root rotted the first one. Then I feared the rest just like usual. Just waiting for them to get to wall and almost hitting me before I cast fear and sic pet.<br />with Extended afflictation. one cast of fear did it.  just a thought for those that like to hunt bank in katta. Root rot first gaurd on left as you face bank with your back against wall. then pull the second gaurd on left, let him come to you. sic pet before he gets to you (not too early since hes now got quick aggro) and then fear him as hes about to hit you, he will turn around and run straight back to his spawn. he should be about dead as he walks past his spawn point. rinse and repeat the other four gaurds (two on the right and two in front of bank). option two which also works and pull the first one the left and aggro him to behind the building on the left then fear kite him. that way he wont aggro the other gaurd on the left. then go back and fear kite the others as usual. There a little bit more risk involved with this and a little more mana intensive, but still very doable. <br /><br />Those that say fear kiting in Katta is gone just haven't tried enough yet. Yes, its no fun to change tactics. But i dont thing Verant is going to have a bleeding heart for us necros.<br /><br />As I look to 60+, i wish that i had leveled sooner :). going to be a little tougher now. Easy AA aint going to be easy anymore! <br /></span></font></td>
